{"title_page": "Rajesh Lilothia", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian politician}}\n\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Rajesh Lilothia\n| honorific-prefix = \n| image = \n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = New Delhi\n| residence = \n| office = Member of Legislative Assembly<br />for [[Patel Nagar (Delhi Assembly constituency)|Patel Nagar]]\n| term_start = 2004\n| term_end = 2013\n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| party = [[Indian National Congress]]\n| spouse = Madhu Lilothia\n| profession = Politician\n| religion = Hindu\n| website = \n| children = Tanvee Lilothia\n}}\n\n'''Rajesh Lilothia'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://delhiassembly.nic.in/aspfile/whos_who/Rajesh_Lilothia.htm|title=Name|website=delhiassembly.nic.in}}</ref> is an Indian politician from [[Delhi]] and former MLA of the [[Delhi Legislative Assembly]] from [[Patel Nagar (Delhi Assembly constituency)|Patel Nagar]] assembly constituency. He was born in a humble Hindu family.  He is a member of the [[Indian National Congress]]. He was the [[Delhi Pradesh Youth Congress]] President from 2001-2006. He held the post of Secretary in [[All India Congress Committee]] and in-charge of Bihar.  He is recently appointed as the Working President of [[Delhi Pradesh Congress Committee]]. \n\n==Education==\nHe completed his graduation from [[Hansraj College]], Delhi University. He post graduated in Disaster Mitigation from [[Sikkim Manipal University]].\n\n==Political career==\n\n===2020 Delhi Legislative Assembly election===\n\n'''Rajesh Lilothia''' was the contested from the [[Mangol Puri (Delhi Assembly constituency)|Mangol Puri]] as a Congress party candidate for [[2020 Delhi Legislative Assembly election]]. But he lost the contest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mangol_Puri_(Delhi_Assembly_constituency)|title=2020 Delhi Legislative Assembly election|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>Raaj Kumar Anand won as AAP candidate.\n===2019 Indian general elections===\n\nHe was contested  [[2019 Indian general election]] as a candidate of [[Indian National Congress]] from [[North West Delhi (Lok Sabha constituency)|North West Delhi]] [[Lok Sabha]] constituency.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/general-election-2019-sheila-dikshit-delhi-congress-chief-to-contest-national-elections-party-releas-2026561|title=General Election 2019: Sheila Dikshit To Contest From Delhi, Congress Names 6 Candidates|website=NDTV.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/congress-announces-6-names-for-delhi-lok-sabha-polls/1520204|title=Congress announces 6 names for Delhi Lok Sabha polls|website=https://www.outlookindia.com/}}</ref> he lost the contest.\n\n<br />\n===2015 Delhi Legislative Assembly election===\n\nHe lost the election in 2015 from [[Patel Nagar (Delhi Assembly constituency)|patel nagar]] . [[Hazari Lal Chauhan]] won this seat as AAP candidate.  \n\n===2013 Delhi Legislative Assembly election===\n\n'''Rajesh Lilothia'''  lost the election. AAP candidate [[Veena Anand]] gain this seat.\n\n<br />\n===2008 Delhi Legislative Assembly election===\n\n'''Rajesh Lilothia'''  won and INC hold  [[Patel Nagar (Delhi Assembly constituency)|patel nagar]] seat.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lilothia, Rajesh}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian politicians]]\n[[Category:Indian National Congress politicians from Delhi]]\n[[Category:Delhi politicians]]\n[[Category:Delhi MLAs 2008\u20132013]]\n\n\n{{INC-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian politician}}\n\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Rajesh Lilothia\n| honorific-prefix = \n| image = \n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = New Delhi\n| residence = \n| office = Member of Legislative Assembly<br />for [[Patel Nagar (Delhi Assembly constituency)|Patel Nagar]]\n| term_start = 2004\n| term_end = 2013\n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| party = [[Indian National Congress]]\n| spouse = Madhu Lilothia\n| profession = Politician\n| religion = Hindu\n| website = \n| children = Tanvee Lilothia\n}}\n\n'''Rajesh Lilothia'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://delhiassembly.nic.in/aspfile/whos_who/Rajesh_Lilothia.htm|title=Name|website=delhiassembly.nic.in}}</ref> is an Indian politician from [[Delhi]] and former MLA of the [[Delhi Legislative Assembly]] from [[Patel Nagar (Delhi Assembly constituency)|Patel Nagar]] assembly constituency. He was born in a humble Hindu family. He completed his graduation from [[Hansraj College]], Delhi University. He post graduated in Disaster Mitigation from [[Sikkim Manipal University]]. He is a member of the [[Indian National Congress]]. He was the [[Delhi Pradesh Youth Congress]] President from 2001-2006. He held the post of Secretary in [[All India Congress Committee]] and in-charge of Bihar.  He is recently appointed as the Working President of [[Delhi Pradesh Congress Committee]]. He is contesting [[2019 Indian general election]] as a candidate of [[Indian National Congress]] from [[North West Delhi (Lok Sabha constituency)|North West Delhi ]] [[Lok Sabha]] constituency.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/general-election-2019-sheila-dikshit-delhi-congress-chief-to-contest-national-elections-party-releas-2026561|title=General Election 2019: Sheila Dikshit To Contest From Delhi, Congress Names 6 Candidates|website=NDTV.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/congress-announces-6-names-for-delhi-lok-sabha-polls/1520204|title=Congress announces 6 names for Delhi Lok Sabha polls|website=https://www.outlookindia.com/}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lilothia, Rajesh}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian politicians]]\n[[Category:Indian National Congress politicians from Delhi]]\n[[Category:Delhi politicians]]\n[[Category:Delhi MLAs 2008\u20132013]]\n\n\n{{INC-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "AakashSharmaHub", "label": "safe", "comment": "Updated more details", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rajesh_Lilothia"}
